  <generalInformation><![CDATA[<p><strong>Beginners</strong> Nursery slopes are in the centre of the village and there are gentle blue runs to progress to.</p>
<p><strong>Intermediates</strong> Virtually all the slopes in the Bad Kleinkirchheim and St. Oswald ski area are ideal for intermediates.</p>
<p><strong>Advanced skiers</strong> will enjoy the beautiful and challenging Franz Klammer downhill run.</p>
<p><strong>Snowboarders</strong> take the Nockalm gondola to St. Oswald for access to the Q Park at nearly 2,000m.</p>
<p><strong>Our favourite run</strong></p>
<p><em>'The Franz Klammer World Cup run - better still if you can ski it hosted by the great man himself on one of his regular and very popular guiding days (pre-bookable). This exciting and challenging run has a gradient of up to 80% and it ends in the midst of the village centre, at the Römerbad thermal spa.' (Anni Mothes, Product Manager Austria)</em></p>]]></generalInformation>
